VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that. So that\'s my prompt. Obviously that\'s pretty concise. So like if you really had a good sub-agent use case, you probably want to give it some more detail and some more nuance there. But I just want to show you how it\'s able to generate this file from the description. And because I chose project level, it\'s'

[12:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'going to create that in the agents folder within my .claude. So in a sec here, we\'ll see an agent pop up. It\'ll probably be called like um devil\'s advocate.md or roast agent.md, something like that. Oh, but before that, it also'

[12:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'says what tools do we want it to be able to use? So like for example, in this one, maybe I only want it to go with read-only tools. So I could say just read-only and then, you know, we could look at some of the advanced options,'

[12:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'too, which would be all these MCP servers and a bunch of other things. And even like individual tools, whoops, even individual tools like bash, cron create, cron delete. Like you can get really granular here. But in this case, I\'m just going to go ahead and hit continue'

[12:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with read-only tools. And then we\'re able to choose the model. And in this case, we\'re going to go with haiku, but you can also inherit from the parent. So if the parent\'s running on haiku, all of the agents that all of that sub-agent will be inherited or same thing with opus or sonnet. And then finally, we can'

[13:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'choose our background color. I\'m just going to go ahead and choose pink. And then we get to choose the memory. So whether that\'s project, none, user, or local. And so really for the sub-agents that I\'d be creating and the ones that I\'d recommend you guys do, I\'d probably'

[13:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just say project scope unless you want all these sub-agents to be completely completely innocent, wake up completely blind, no memory at all, then you would choose none. But as far as between project, user, and local, I\'m probably just going to always choose project. All'

[13:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'right, there we go. So, I\'m going to go ahead and save this new agent, and you can see it just popped up right here. It\'s called the plan roster. And what happens when you create them with Claude is it makes this huge because it doesn\'t yet understand what you might say and'

[13:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'how you want it to trigger. So, my first recommendation would be trim this down a little bit because once again, this is part of the progressive disclosure. So, there\'s no need for the description to be so long. So, I\'m literally going to delete all of this. I'

[13:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'mean, it\'s good to look at, but I\'m going to delete all of this up to here. And really in my case, this is good enough, right? Use this agent when Nate wants an adversarial critique of an idea, plan, strategy, blah blah blah. Trigger on phrases like roast my plan or review my plan. We\'ve got the tools, the'

[14:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'model, the color, the memory, and the name. So, now I\'m just going to open up a new session of Claude, and um let\'s real quick just say So, I\'ve got this plan, and I want to create an ice cream stand in you know, uh Chicago. I want to create'

[14:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this ice cream stand on Oak Street Beach. And I don\'t yet have a refrigerator, and I want to sell the ice cream all day long for about you know, 20 bucks a pop. And it\'s just'

[14:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
